SIMPLE: stivation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Æstivation
<hw>⟦AE⟧s`ti*va"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The state of torpidity induced by the heat and
dryness of summer, as in certain snails; -- opposed to
<contr>hibernation</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The arrangement of the petals in a
flower bud, as to folding, overlapping, etc.; prefloration.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><altsp>[Spelt also <asp>estivation</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>AEstuary</ent>⟦br⟧
